inglePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528811\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528811\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Nov 13, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jdg1665702597130.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jdg1665702597130.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jdg1665702597130.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"jdg1665702597130\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      /bat\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Start the application in batch mode.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jdg1665702597130__section_w2108ab1b5b1_w2109ab1b5_w2110ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jdg1665702597130__p_d148007e1_d148008e1_d148009e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/bat</span> {<var class=\"keyword varname\">param_1</var>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">param_2</var> ...}</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jdg1665702597130__section_hjg_jgb_hhc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d606959e66\">Use With</h2>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"jdg1665702597130__ul_gjr_4bj_hhc\">\n<li class=\"li\">ide.exe (Uniface IDE: /bat /tst only)</li>\n<li class=\"li\">User applications</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jdg1665702597130__section_w2114ab1b5b5_w2115ab1b5_w2116ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d606959e84\">\n                  \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jdg1665702597130__p_d148019e1_d148020e1_d148021e1\">Start the application in batch mode. An application running in batch mode has the following characteristics:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jdg1665702597130__li_d51419e1_d51420e1_d51421e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jdg1665702597130__p_d148022e1_d148023e1_d148024e1\">User input is not possible. You should avoid executing ProcScript statements that require user input, such as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">askmess</span> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">print/ask</code>.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jdg1665702597130__li_d51422e1_d51423e1_d51424e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jdg1665702597130__p_d148025e1_d148026e1_d148027e1\">Output to the screen is not allowed. You should avoid executing ProcScript statements that request screen output, such as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">edit</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">display</span>, and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">message</span>.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jdg1665702597130__li_d51425e1_d51426e1_d51427e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jdg1665702597130__p_d148028e1_d148029e1_d148030e1\">The message frame is disabled. Messages normally sent to the message frame (with the ProcScript statement <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">putmess</span>, for example) are redirected to the standard system output device. This is usually the terminal screen.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jdg1665702597130__li_d51428e1_d51429e1_d51430e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jdg1665702597130__p_d148031e1_d148032e1_d148033e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/tfo</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/tfi</span> switches are not allowed.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jdg1665702597130__p_d148034e1_d148035e1_d148036e1\">Optionally, you can provide one or more parameters to the batch application via general variables ($1-$99). The first parameter is available in <code class=\"ph codeph\">$1</code>, the second in <code class=\"ph codeph\">$2</code>, and so on. The parameters do not need to directly follow the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/bat</span> switch.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jdg1665702597130__p_d148037e1_d148038e1_d148039e1\">You can use the ProcScript function <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$batch</span> to test if an application is running in batch or interactively.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dic1665702596168.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$batch</a><p>Return the batch mode indicator.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mfp1665702597206.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Passing Parameters to an Application</a><p>The parameters to be passed to your application must be the last parameters entered on the command line.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528811\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528811\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "/bat Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Nov 13, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 /bat Start the application in batch mode. /bat { param_1 param_2 ...} Use With ide.exe (Uniface IDE: /bat /tst only) User applications Description Start the application in batch mode. An application running in batch mode has the following characteristics: User input is not possible. You should avoid executing ProcScript statements that require user input, such as askmess and print/ask . Output to the screen is not allowed. You should avoid executing ProcScript statements that request screen output, such as edit , display , and message . The message frame is disabled. Messages normally sent to the message frame (with the ProcScript statement putmess , for example) are redirected to the standard system output device. This is usually the terminal screen. The /tfo and /tfi switches are not allowed. Optionally, you can provide one or more parameters to the batch application via general variables ($1-$99). The first parameter is available in $1 , the second in $2 , and so on. The parameters do not need to directly follow the /bat switch. You can use the ProcScript function $batch to test if an application is running in batch or interactively. Related Links $batch Return the batch mode indicator. Passing Parameters to an Application The parameters to be passed to your application must be the last parameters entered on the command line. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}